-- England Scores 425 in 2nd Test vs South Africa, Leads by 6 Runs
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-08-05T11:43:09Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-05/england-scores-425-in-2nd-test-vs-south-africa-leads-by-6-runs.html
England was dismissed for 425 in its
first innings on the penultimate day of the second cricket Test
against South Africa, a lead of six runs.   Top-scorer  Kevin Pietersen  was dismissed for 149, failing
to add to his overnight score. Matt Prior hit 68 runs.  South Africa leads 1-0 in the three-game contest. The
Proteas can replace England at the top of the International
Cricket Council Test rankings by winning the series.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  